THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 252300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING AN ANTI-CYCLONE 1033 CENTRED IN SEA
AREA HEBRIDES EXTENDING EWARDS ACROSS SCOTLAND INTO THE N
SEA. BY MIDDAY FRIDAY THE CENTRE OF THE ANTI-CYCLONE WILL
HAVE TRANSFERRED EWARDS INTO THE CENTRAL N SEA FM WHERE
IT WILL SLWY DECLINE S-EWARDS INTO THE CONTINENT.
OVERNIGHT THURSDAY INTO FRIDAY AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
1008 CENTRED W OF SEA AREA FITZROY WILL REMAIN SLOW MOV
AND DEEPEN A LITTLE BEFORE SLWY DRIFTING NWARDS TO BE
CENTRED OVER SEA AREA BAILEY 1003 BY MIDDAY SUNDAY
THEREAFTER IT FILLS AND DRIFTS AWAY N-EWARDS.
STRG WINDS WILL AFFECT THE EERN N SEA ON THURSDAY NIGHT
PERHAPS REACHING NEAR GALE STRENGTH IN SEA AREA FISHER
WITH STRG NE WINDS ALSO EXP THROUGH THE ENGLISH CHANNEL.
THESE STRG WINDS WILL PERSIST THROUGH THURSDAY NIGHT BUT
SLWY EASE LATER ON FRIDAY AND OVERNIGHT INTO SATURDAY. NO
HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ELSEWHERE IN CULLERCOATS.
